==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Usance
<hw>Us"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See <er>Use</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Use; usage; employment.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Custom; practice; usage.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Gower. Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Interest paid for money; usury.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Com.)</fld> <def>The time, fixed variously by the
usage between different countries, when a bill of exchange is payable;
<as>as, a bill drawn on London at one <ex>usance</ex>, or at double
<ex>usance</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Usant</ent>⟦br⟧
